

filter / Query Operators

        -@eq: equal 1 = 1
        -@ne: not equal 1 != 2
        -@gt: greater than 2 > 1
        -@gte: greater than or equal 2 >= 2
        -@lt: less than 1 < 2
        -@lte: less than or equal 2 <= 2
        -@in: in array 
        -@nin: not in array



        -@and: logical AND  1 or more conditions must be true
        -@or: logical OR   1 or more conditions must be true
        -@nor: logical NOR  none of the conditions must be true
        -@not: negate filter inverse of the array expression

         

        -@regex: regular expression
        -@where: JavaScript expression




        -@options: regular expression options (i, m, s, u, y)
        -@elemMatch: match array elements
        -@size: size of array
        -@all: match all elements in array
        -@exists: field exists
        -@type: field type
        -@expr: use aggregation expression
        -@jsonSchema: validate against JSON Schema
        -@text: text search
        
